# Canvas App Locator Conventions

The app renders ENTIRELY inside `iframe[name="fullscreen-app-host"]`. Every locator MUST
go through the frame first. NEVER write locators directly on the page for Canvas elements.

```ts
const appFrame = page.frameLocator('iframe[name="fullscreen-app-host"]');
await expect.soft(appFrame.getByRole('button', { name: 'Dashboard' })).toBeVisible();
```

## Rules

- Controls are ABSOLUTELY-POSITIONED SIBLINGS, not visually nested. Do NOT scope a control by
  its on-screen label's parent (e.g. `xpath=//div[.="Region"]/..`) — the label and the control
  are separate siblings, so that resolves to nothing. Locate the control directly by role/name.
- After opening a screen, WAIT for real data to load (e.g. a data row) before
  asserting on late-rendering controls — several controls (dropdowns, pagination) render after
  the grid. Add a data-row wait to navigation helpers.
- Dropdowns (period / Region) render as `getByRole('button', { name })` and open a
  `getByRole('option', { name })` listbox. Selected value becomes the button name (e.g.
  `. This Month`); an unselected Region shows the placeholder name `.` (unique on the screen).
- Match the app's ACTUAL text, including typos (e.g. period options are `Quater to Date` /
  `Last Quater`, not "Quarter").
- Use `getByRole` and `getByText`. NEVER use auto-generated CSS IDs or appmagic IDs.
- `getByLabel` does NOT work in Canvas apps — use `getByPlaceholder` or `getByText`.
- Canvas toggles are custom controls — click the label text to toggle them.
- Canvas rich text areas are contenteditable — use `.fill()` then assert `toHaveValue()`.
- Delete buttons are image icons — use `getByRole('img')`, NOT `getByRole('button')`.
- NEVER hardcode counts — use regex, e.g. `appFrame.getByText(/\d+\s*Drafts/)`.
- Use `expect.soft` for UI structure visibility assertions.
- Use hard `expect` for interaction and navigation assertions.
- NEVER use `waitForTimeout` except inside the `getDashboardTaskCount` helper.
- Never wait for `networkidle` or use deprecated/discouraged APIs.

## Authentication

Auth is handled via `storageState` in `playwright.config.ts`. Tests NEVER include a login
step — the saved session handles it. NEVER add login code to any test file.
`auth.json` and `auth/` must NEVER be committed (already in `.gitignore`).

## Live MCP exploration (planner / generator)

When driving the app live via the `playwright-test` MCP, the Canvas content lives inside the
iframe, so top-level readiness checks do NOT see it:

- Do NOT use `browser_wait_for({ text: "Dashboard" })` — text inside the iframe is invisible
  to the top-level page, so it hangs until timeout.
- Instead, after `browser_navigate`, use a timed settle then snapshot:
  `browser_wait_for({ time: 10 })` then `browser_snapshot`. The snapshot DOES include iframe
  content (nodes appear with `f1e*` refs).
- Refs (`f1e*`) go stale when the frame re-renders. Re-`browser_snapshot` before clicking if
  a ref is "not found".
- This applies only to live exploration; generated test code still uses
  `frameLocator('iframe[name="fullscreen-app-host"]')`, which correctly enters the frame.
